<TITLE> Mirpur mob runs amok as bus kills child </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 18 (bdnews24.com)  Locals in the capital's Mirpur area ran amok Thursday night after an eight year-old boy was run over and killed by a BTRC bus, said police. At least 20 vehicles were vandalised in a mob attack following the accident, at around 8:45pm, near Al-Helal Hospital between Mirpur-10 roundabout and Kazipara, officer in charge of Mirpur police station Nazim Uddin told bdnews24.com. The BTRC busDhaka Metro-B-11-1468ran over the boy as he was crossing the road in front of Kazipara Sonali Bank with his mother to go to Al-Helal Hospital, said witnesses. The boy, whose name was given as 'Nabin' by police and witnesses, died on the spot, they said. In an outrage, locals and passersby wrecked dozens of 50 vehicles and brought traffic to a halt on Rokeya Swarani up to 10pm, he also said. Police later brought the situation under control. The boy's body was sent to Dhaka Medical College Hospital morgue, said police. bd
